## Rule Update Guide

| Area | File |
|---|---|
| Language policy | `rules/language.md` |
| Agent Teams workflow | `rules/agent-teams.md` |
| Skill auto-activation (stack-agnostic) | `rules/skill-activation.md` |
| Git workflow (branching / commits / PR) | `rules/git-workflow.md` |
| ADR discipline | `rules/adr.md` |
| Security baseline | `rules/security.md` |
| Stack-specific mappings | `rules/stacks/<stack>.md` |

## Stack Rules (project CLAUDE.md opt-in)

Global makes no stack assumption. Each project CLAUDE.md opts in to the stacks it uses.

```markdown
# <project> Rules

@~/.claude/rules/stacks/nextjs.md
@~/.claude/rules/stacks/supabase.md
```

Available: `nextjs`, `supabase`, `vercel`, `cloudflare`, `playwright`, `claude-api`, `sentry`, `amplitude`, `vitest`, `tailwind`, `resend`, `github-actions`
